  "text": "The principal's predecessor took office in 1982 and he retired at the end of 2009. The new principal was appointed in 2010. This new principal had been the principal of a nearby high school and his two sons had previously attended the school in the study. This implied that the principal had developed constructs of the previous principal and the school prior to his appointment [CITATION_1] . As valuable as these experiences were, they could not prepare him sufficiently for the post. Recalling his experience as high school principal, which also revealed his leadership approach, the principal explained: \"I was … definitely a bit autocratic as far as the school work and academic work were concerned\".",
